         Findings with Splurt, 3 tests done, no focus item equipped.</P><P>Initial HP: 2973<BR>Tick #  HP<BR>1 2972<BR>2 2962<BR>3 2943<BR>4 2915<BR>5 2878<BR>6 2832<BR>7 2777<BR>8 2713<BR>9 2640<BR>10 2558<BR>11 2467<BR>12 2367<BR>13 2258<BR>14 2140<BR>15 2013<BR>16 1877</P><P>TOTAL DMG: 1096<BR>W/ REGEN: 1208 [1096 + (7*16)]<BR>W/ PVP: 1830 [1208 / .66]</P><P>This time it did the correct number of ticks per the SPDat, but the damage is screwy.</P><P>The SPDat entry for Splurt doesn't give any information about Splurt's damage (Unknown Formula), but I've always assumed it did about 1700 damage.  A 7.723 DPM rating is EXTREMELY nice, and more than we've ever assumed about it.</P><P>So, math heads, what did I do rong here.  The data above is right, I casted at full health (2973/2973) and ended up (1877/2973) when Splurt wore off.  My standing hp regeneration is 7 (normal regen + 3 AA).  The PvP damage reduction is 66% exactly, correct?</P><P>Daedrea Darksoul<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
