        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Wouldn't casting a DD spell on someone tell you what the PvP damage reduction was?</P><P>If you don't enter HP regeneration into the equation, you still end up with the total damage for Pyrocruor being 2160 and Splurt being a more reasonable 1660.  However, you can't simply ignore the HP regen.  It had to have factored in to some extent.  If you put the HP regeneration in AFTER the PvP damage reduction you get:</P><P>Pyrocruor<BR>Total DMG: 1426<BR>PvP Damge Reduction: 2160 [1426 / 0.66]<BR>HP Regeneration: 2293 [2160 + (7*19)]</P><P>Splurt<BR>Total DMG: 1096<BR>PvP Damage Reduction: 1660 [1096 / 0.66]<BR>HP Regeneration: 1772 [1660 + (7*16)]</P><P>Very close to the original numbers, and a good bit higher than previously suspected, especially for Pyro.  I'm gonna go in and test CoC now and see what I come up with.  Very interesting to say the least.</P><P>As for the additional ticks, every single time I casted Pyro on myself it came up with 19 ticks.  Every single time I casted Splurt it was 16.  There was no variation with anything.</P><P>Daedrea Darksoul<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
