        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'm surprised none of you remember the DoT nerf/buff years ago.  Years ago they added a change to DoTs where if the mob was moving the entire fight it did a third less damage than what is in the SPDAT.  On the other side if the mob was stationary the complete time it did a third MORE damage than what the spell was set at in the SPDAT.  Go to eq.castersrealm.com and look in the patch message archives, or perhaps a really outdated druid messageboard (they considered it a big nerf to them, whereas necromancers considered it a buff to us).</P><P>Ualdayan, Lvl59 Defiler<BR>Bristlebane</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
