        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>change to DoTs where if the mob was moving the entire fight it did a third less damage than what is in the SPDAT. On the other side if the mob was stationary the complete time it did a third MORE damage <BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>The first part is partially true, if the mob is moving towards what is aggroed upon it does 66% of normal damage.  However if it is moving away (fear or low hp run mode) it works normally.</P><P>The second part about 33% more damage if standing still is completely incorrect.</P><P>Yes, there was a slight enhancement of dots that existed at that point but it was simply by extending their max duration by one tick to cover up to 3 ticks of movement by the mob.  Thus if the mob only moved 2 or less ticks during the entire new duration of the dot there would be a slight increase in total damage.  This assumes of course the dot has time to run its full duration, a fundamental problem/oversight we're still struggling with.</P><P>Ever wondered why Ignite Blood and Plague are 2 minutes + 6 seconds or Cascading darkness 90 seconds + 6 seconds?  Thats why, they existed at the point the dot change/nerf was made and got the extra tick of duration.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
